*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|сем}}, {{t|sh|осим}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|sem}}, {{t+|sh|osim}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|okrem}}, {{t|sk|len}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|rázen}}\n* Sotho: {{t|st|ha e se}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|excepto}}, {{t+|es|salvo}}, {{t+|es|sino}}, {{t+|es|mas}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|förutom}}, {{t+|sv|utom}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|maliban}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|hariç}}, {{t+|tr|başka}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|крім}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|ac eithrio}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|la}}, {{t|zza|nara}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|solely, only, merely (obsolete)}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|ancaq}}, {{t|az|təkcə}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|бен}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|只|tr=zhǐ}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|que}}, {{t+|fr|seulement}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|somente}}, {{t|gl|namais}}, {{t|gl|xiquera}}\n* German: {{t+|de|nur}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|csak}}, {{t+|hu|csupán}}, {{t+|hu|mindössze}}, {{t+|hu|pusztán}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|だけ|tr=dake}}, {{t+|ja|しか|tr=shika}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|tik}}, {{t+|lt|vos}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|būtan}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|doar}}, {{t+|ro|numai}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|то́лько}}, {{t+|ru|лишь}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|len}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sólo}}, {{t+|es|solamente}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|بس|tr=bas}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|teyna}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Arabic: {{t+check|ar|بَل}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t-check|grc|ἀλλά}}\n* Hungarian: {{t-check|hu|[[kivéve]] [[-t]], [[csak]]}} (after a negative sentence), {{t-check|hu|[[csak]] [[nem]]}} (after a positive sentence)\n* Indonesian: {{t+check|id|tapi}}, {{t+check|id|tetapi}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+check|kmr|lê}} {{q|Kurmanji}}\n* Old Prussian: {{t-check|prg|aber}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t-check|fa-ira|وَلی}}\n* Tamil: {{t+check|ta|ஆனால்}}\n* Telugu: {{t+check|te|కానీ}}\n* Volapük: {{t+check|vo|ab}}, {{t+check|vo|efe}}, {{t+check|vo|sod}} (archaic)\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# An [[instance#Noun|instance]] of using the word \"but\"; an [[objection#Noun|objection]] or [[caveat#Noun|caveat]].\n#: {{ux|en|It has to be done—no ifs, ands, or '''buts'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|But—and this is a big '''but'''—you have to come home by sundown.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=1922-03-04|title=Fed on Fear Too Much|journal=The Pathfinder|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=Pathfinder Publishing Company|volume=29|issue=1470|page=33|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/sim_town-journal_1922-03-04_29_1470/page/32/mode/2up?q=%22buts+and+nots%22|passage=The children are taught to be afraid of winter, of war, of death, of hard times, of disease, of examtinations. Perhaps that is one of the reasons that children so seldom find the conversation of their elders uplifting. It is full of don’ts, '''buts''' and nots.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Concepcion de Leon|title=5 Things Well-Meaning People Say to Me That Are Actually Really Offensive|work=[[w:Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230208093938/https://www.glamour.com/story/5-things-well-meaning-people-say-to-me-that-are-actually-really-offensive|location=Greenwich, C.T.;{{nb...|New York, N.Y.; Los Angeles, C.A.}}|publisher=[[w:Condé Nast|Condé Nast Publications]]|date=28 December 2016|issn=0017-0747|oclc=5259082|passage=\"I support you/understand where you're coming from, but...\" ¶ No. No \"'''buts'''\" when it comes to other people's survival.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Catriona Harvey-Jenner|title=8 foods you should never eat before a workout|work=[[w:Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128234014/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/body/diet-nutrition/a23280061/foods-never-eat-before-workout/|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Hearst Communications|date=17 September 2018|issn=0010-9541|oclc=1770745|passage=But - and this is a pretty important '''but''' - it's just as bad to eat the ''wrong'' thing before a workout as it is to eat nothing at all.}}\n# {{lb|en|Scotland}} The [[outer]] [[room]] of a small two-room [[cottage]].\n# A [[limit]]; a [[boundary]].\n# The end; especially the larger or thicker end, or the blunt, in distinction from the sharp, end; the [[butt]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|top and but}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|++}}\n\n# {{lb|en|archaic}} Use the word \"but\".\n#: {{ux|en|'''But''' me no buts.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|en|title=Terms derived from the preposition, adverb, conjunction, or noun ''but''|all but|but and ben|but good|ifs, ands, or buts|but that|can but hope|all-but|anything but|but for|but for the grace of God|but hey|but if|but me no buts|but seriously folks|but then|but then again|but who's counting|cannot but|cannot help but|gurry-but|not but|not only … but also|nothing but|though but|can't but|can't help but|everything but the galley stove|it's not what you know but whom you know|it's not what you say but how you say it|Jill of all trades but mistress of none|silent-but-violent|yesterday but one}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=btu|BTU|TBU|tub}}\n\n{{cln|en|coordinating conjunctions|focus adverbs|3-letter words}}\n\n==Cornish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|kw|en|butt}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{kw-noun|m|ys}}\n\n# {{lb|kw|archery}} {{l|en|butt}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{kw-mut}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:CDGK}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|da|gml|butt}}.\n\n===Adjective===\n{{da-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|da|rare}} [[blunt]]\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-infl-adj|butt}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|stump}}\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|da|spids}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{der|fr|frm|but||mark, goal}}, from {{der|fr|fro|but||aim, goal, end, target}}, from {{der|fr|fro|butte||mound, knoll, target}}, from {{der|fr|frk|*but||stump, log}}, or from {{der|fr|non|bútr||log, stump, butt}}; both from {{der|fr|gem-pro|*buttaz||end, piece}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|ang|butt||tree stump}}; see {{m|en|butt}}. The semantic development from \"mound\" to \"target\" is likely from [[martial]] training practice. The final {{IPAchar|/t/}} is from the old pausal and liaison pronunciation; its (partial) restoration as the basic form may have been reinforced by related {{m|fr|butte}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{fr-IPA|butt|a=outside Canada now more often}}\n** {{homophones|fr|bute|butent|butes|bûtes|buts|butte|buttent|buttes}}\n** {{audio|fr|Fr-but.ogg}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[aim]]\n# [[goal]] {{gloss|result one is attempting to achieve}}\n# {{lb|fr|sports}} [[goal]] {{gloss|in the place, act, or point sense}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{l|fr|fin}}\n* {{l|fr|objectif}}\n* {{l|fr|dessein}}\n* {{l|fr|point}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|fr\n|but cadré\n|but contre son camp\n|but en argent\n|but en or\n|buter\n|buteur\n|buteuse\n|coup de pied de but\n|de but en blanc\n|deuxième but\n|droit au but\n|gardien de but\n|gardienne de but\n|premier but\n|tirs au but\n|troisième but\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{m|fr|boire}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{homophones|fr|bu|bue|bues|bus|bût|buts}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|boire||3|s|phis}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n{{C|fr|Football (soccer)|Handball|Hockey}}\n{{cln|fr|terms with irregularly sounded consonant}}\n\n==Iban==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|iba|adjective}}\n\n# [[stinky]]\n\n==Indonesian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|id|computing}} [[bootstrap]] (process by which the operating system of a computer is loaded into its memory)\n\n===References===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Maltese==\n{{mt-root|b-w-t}}\n\n===Etymology===\nProbably from {{inh|mt|ar|بُوطَة}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|mt|/buːt/}}\n* {{rhymes|mt|uːt|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{mt-noun|g=m|p=bwiet|dim=bwejjet|dim2=buta|dim3=bwejta}}\n\n# [[pocket]]\n# {{lb|mt|figuratively}} [[money]]\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|būtan}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*biūtan}}, {{m|gmw-pro|*biūtini}}, equivalent to {{af|enm|be-|out|nocat=1}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|enm|bute|buten|boute|bouten}}\n* {{alter|enm|botte|bot|bod}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|enm|/but/}}\n\n====Conjunction====\n{{head|enm|conjunction}}\n\n# {{l|en|but}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|but}}\n* {{desc|sco|but}}\n* {{desc|yol|mot}}\n\n=====References=====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=but|pos=conj|id=MED6406}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|Northern ME}} {{alt form|enm|bote|t=boot|id=boot}}\n\n[[Category:Northern Middle English]]\n\n==Old Polish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{zlw-opl-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{zlw-opl-noun|m-in}}\n\n# {{alt form|zlw-opl|bot}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n[[File:Black Converse sneakers.JPG|thumb|buty]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|pl|bot||Middle Polish}}\n* {{alt|pl|bót||obsolete|or|dialectal|Lubawa}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|pl|id=shoe|:inh|zlw-opl:bot<id:shoe>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|pl|zlw-opl|bot}}, which see for more on the change in the vowel.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-but.ogg;LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-but.wav|hh=bud|mp=#|suw=#|CD=#}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-in,m-anml|dim=bucik,butek|aug=bucior,bucisko}}\n\n# [[shoe]]\n## [[boot]] {{gl|heavy shoe that covers part of the leg}}\n# {{lb|pl|Chełmno|unit of measure}} {{syn of|pl|stopa}}\n# {{lb|pl|construction|sailing}} [[keel]] [[block]] {{gl|wooden base on which the support that holds the ship's hull during rests for construction}}\n# [[pile shoe]] {{gl|metal tip to a pole that is to be driven into the ground}}\n# {{lb|pl|Chełmno|Suwałki|unit of measure}} {{syn of|pl|stopa}}\n# {{lb|pl|obsolete|jocular|in the plural}} [[seventy seven]] {{gl|the number 77 is a game of chance}}\n# {{lb|pl|Middle Polish}} [[boot]] {{gl|horse leg protector, worn for therapeutic purposes}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-anml|accs=but/buta}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adverbs|pod butem|z buta}}\n{{col|pl|title=interjections|takie buty}}\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|czyścibut|łyżka do butów|pucybut|półbut|siedmiomilowe buty}}\n{{col|pl|title=particles|}}\n{{col|pl|title=phrases|buty pospadały|buty z nóg spadają|słoma z butów wystaje|umarł w butach}}\n{{col|pl|title=prepositions|pod butem}}\n{{col|pl|title=proverbs|idzie luty, podkuj buty|szewc bez butów chodzi|trza być w butach na weselu}}\n{{pl-derived verbs\n|wyrwać z butów/wyrywać z butów\n|-/kiwać palcem w bucie\n|uszyć buty/szyć buty\n|wejść w buty/wchodzić w buty\n|wejść z butami/wchodzić z butami}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP||1971}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n* {{R:pl:SXVI|+|44644}}\n* {{R:pl:SXVII|BUT|8122||28.04.2010}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1807}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1861}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1900||240|1}}\n* {{R:pl:SGP1900||143|1}}\n* {{R:pl:NFJP}}\n* {{R:pl:Nitsch:1907||387}}\n\n{{C|pl|Footwear|Units of measure}}\n\n==Romani==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|rom|pra-sau|𑀩𑀳𑀼𑀢𑁆𑀢}},<ref name=\"bi\">{{R:rom:Boretzky-Igla|but|page=39b}}</ref> from {{inh|rom|sa|बहुत्व|t=much, many, very}}.<ref name=\"bi\"/><ref name=\"t\">{{R:CDIAL|bahutva|9190|page=519}}</ref> Cognate with {{cog|hi|बहुत}}.\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|rom|adjective|oblique|bute|cat2=1-syllable words}}\n\n# [[much]]<ref name=\"bi\"/><ref name=\"t\"/><ref name=\"cI\">{{R:Courthiade:2009|entry=but B-ćham: -e I|page=97a}}</ref><ref name=\"s\">{{R:NERG+|entry=but|page=147}}</ref>\n# [[many]]<ref name=\"bi\"/><ref name=\"t\"/><ref name=\"cI\"/>\n#: {{ux|rom|'''But''' rroma mekhle i India thaj gele p-e aver phuva.''|t='''Many''' Roma left India and went towards other lands.}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|rom|adverb}}\n\n# [[very]]<ref name=\"bi\"/><ref name=\"s\"/><ref>{{R:Courthiade:2009|entry=but II|page=97a}}</ref>\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|ota|بوت|tr=but}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|n|buturi}}\n\n# [[thigh]] of an animal\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-n-uri}}\n\n==Scots==\n\n===Noun===\n{{sco-noun}}\n\n# The [[outer]] [[room]] of a small two-room [[cottage]].\n\n===Preposition===\n{{h|sco|prep}}\n\n# [[outside|Outside]] of, [[without]].\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sh|ota|بوت|tr=but}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sh|/bût/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-noun|bȕt|m-in}}\n\n# [[thigh]]\n# [[ham]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|bȕt|bùtovi\n|bùta|butova\n|butu|butovima\n|but|butove\n|bute|butovi\n|butu|butovima\n|butom|butovima\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:sh:HJP|f11kURA%3D}}\n\n==Turkish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|tr|bud||dialectal}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|tr|ota|بود|tr=bud}}, {{m|ota|بوت|tr=but}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*būt}}. Compare {{cog|otk|tr=būt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|tr|LL-Q256 (tur)-ToprakM-but.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tr-noun|u|lar}}\n\n# [[thigh]]\n#: {{syn|tr|uyluk}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{tr-infl-noun-c|u|poss=1}}\n\n==Volapük==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|vo|/but/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{vo-noun}}\n\n# [[boot]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{vo-decl-noun}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:vo:Vödabuk}}\n\n{{C|vo|Footwear}}"}}